      • saveResult

        public static void saveResult(java.lang.String result,
                              java.lang.String[] savedResults)
        This method saves specific operation results on the first space of an array, and moves the other space's result one space forwards. Pre: The result is in String type. The array is a String array. The array is instantiated. Post: The result is saved on the first space and the other results are one space forwards.
        Parameters:
        result. - Result to save. Cannot be a result of hexadecimal conversion, binary conversion and scientific notation conversion. Cannot be empty.
        savedResults. - Array that will store to result. Defined to hold 10 spaces.

      • getResult

        public static java.lang.String getResult(java.lang.String numberOne,
                                         java.lang.String[] savedResults)
        This method loads a result stored in an array. Pre: The result requested isn't null. The array is instantiated. The result requested is in range of the array. Post: The result is loaded from the array. An "empty" result is loaded, promping an error.
        Parameters:
        numberOne. - Requested space result. Cannot be empty or null. Must have numbers next to a '$'. Those numbers cannot be greater than 10.
        savedResults. - Array with stored results. Cannot have empty spaces.
        Returns:
        The result in the space position requested by the user.

      • printResults

        public static void printResults(java.lang.String[] savedResults)
        This method prints the results saved in an array. Pre: The array is instantiated. Post: The results are printed on screen.
        Parameters:
        savedResults. - Array with results saved.
